@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_DesignTradeoffs> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_DesignTradeoffs> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#DesignTradeoffs> ;
    narr:childCount "10"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "0a523aa51715f1fd8d96b90b546dd15cfcb11ecf" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers recurring design tensions across vocabulary, architecture, and memory boundaries. A foundational structural pair is [introspect and annotate as inverted complements](narr:Observation_InvertedComplement) operating on the same graph from opposite directions, with an open [scope-vs-introspect tradeoff](narr:Position_ScopeVsIntrospect) still unresolved. Vocabulary is actively contested: [Scarlet's frustration with 'compile' as a tool name](narr:Obs_CoreFrustrationCompile) (Jul 2025) and her later [transform-over-query canonical statement](narr:Obs_TransformVerbQuote) (Apr 2026) reframe the operation as shifting focus, removing triples, or reweighting — not retrieving. A parallel thread concerns what belongs in a memory: [directional-and-relational 'how'](narr:Obs_ScarletQuote_RealDifference) (we did it this way, I asked this person, here is the why) versus implementation detail, with [text hierarchy, ratio, and emotional feeling as perspective](narr:Obs_ScarletQuote_TextHierarchy) but pixel values excluded. A newer anti-reductionist constraint enters in Jun 2026: [the theme-is-interpretive trap](narr:Obs_ThemeIsInterpretiveQuote) — claims can be read multiple ways, and collapsing to a single theme is itself the problem. Two Jun 2026 children introduce a technology-regret thread: [shared RDF-over-Datomic regret](narr:Narrative_RDFOverDatomicRegret) and [a consultant's verbatim expression of that regret](narr:Obs_RDFDatomicRegret), framing Datomic's ergonomics as a missed RDF intersection. [IRI-expansion-at-the-leaves](narr:Obs_IRILeaves) is noted as a stated design goal not yet built.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_RDFOverDatomicRegret> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CoreFrustrationCompile> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_IRILeaves> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_RDFDatomicRegret> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletQuote_RealDifference> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletQuote_TextHierarchy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ThemeIsInterpretiveQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TransformVerbQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_InvertedComplement> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ScopeVsIntrospect> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the problem becomes that theme is interpretive - ie claims can be read different ways, and reducing a claim to a single theme is exactly the kind of reductionism" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ThemeIsInterpretiveQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "We're really taking the existing perspective and shifting the focus... In some cases, that is removing triples. In other cases, it might be changing the weighting of things." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TransformVerbQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the how that belongs in a memory is directional and relational (we did it this way, I asked this person, here is the why). Specifics of code, color values, layout are implementation details." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletQuote_RealDifference> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "IRI-expansion-at-the-leaves: stated design goal, not yet built" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_IRILeaves> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "If Datomic had RDF standardization with its ergonomics, it would have been a wonderful intersection." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_RDFOverDatomicRegret> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The transform-vs-query framing (Apr 2026) reframes the core operation away from retrieval entirely — in tension with any child that treats the system primarily as a query or lookup tool." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TransformVerbQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The theme-is-interpretive constraint (Jun 2026) pushes against any design that assigns single-theme labels to claims — a structural challenge to indexing and routing approaches elsewhere in the graph." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ThemeIsInterpretiveQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The RDF-over-Datomic regret thread (Jun 2026) introduces a technology-choice counterfactual — a road-not-taken framing absent from earlier design tradeoff children." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_RDFOverDatomicRegret> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_RDFDatomicRegret> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "IRI-expansion-at-the-leaves is flagged as aspirational but unbuilt — a gap between stated design intent and current implementation." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_IRILeaves> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}